      "properties": {"Node name for S&R": "Note"},
      "widgets_values": [
        "LIP-SYNC POST-FX PIPELINE (Face-Restore First)\n=========================================\n\nPIPELINE ORDER:\n  1. CodeFormer face restoration (cleans lip-sync artifacts on mouth/eyes)\n  2. RIFE frame interp (25fps → 50fps, smoother motion)\n  3. Deflicker (smooth brightness jumps common in Sonic output)\n  4. LUT color grade (cinematic look)\n  5. 4x UltraSharp upscale\n  6. Pixel cap to 2048\n  7. Blend graded + upscaled (50/50)\n  8. Film grain (subtle, 0.15)\n  9. Save H.264 CRF 16 @ 50fps with original audio preserved\n\nWHY CODEFORMER FIRST?\n  Sonic can produce subtle artifacts around the mouth and eyes,\n  especially on extreme expressions. CodeFormer restores the face\n  cleanly BEFORE any other processing, so subsequent steps work on\n  clean pixels. CodeFormer's weight 0.7 is balanced — higher (0.9)\n  over-smooths skin, lower (0.5) leaves artifacts.\n\nWIDGET NOTES:\n- CodeFormer: weight 0.7, background_restore true (don't blur bg),\n  face_detection 'retinaface' (most reliable).\n- RIFE: multiplier=2 (25→50fps). Use multiplier=4 for 100fps (overkill).\n- Deflicker: gentle settings (0.5) to not kill natural expression changes.\n- Upscale: 4x-UltraSharp ideal for faces. For body scenes, 4x_NMKD-Siax.\n- LUT: 0.9 strength for cohesive grade. Drop to 0.6 for more natural look.\n\n16GB VRAM TIPS:\n  • CodeFormer: ~2GB → very safe\n  • RIFE 512x512: ~3GB → safe\n  • 4x upscale 512x512 → 2048x2048 per frame: ~5GB → safe\n  • All nodes together: ~10GB peak → fits comfortably on 16GB\n\nUSAGE:\n  Run this workflow on EACH lipsync MP4 from workflow 01.\n  Use scripts/batch_render_lipsync.py with --post-fx flag — it auto-routes\n  lipsync scenes to this workflow, broll scenes to 05_standard_postfx.json."
      ],
